description:
**Problem**
PR #2 (perf-optimizations) rewrites src/daemon/run.rs accept loop from non-blocking polling to blocking accept + signal wake pattern. bd-4rhy adds span propagation to spawned threads, but targets the old structure.

**Design**
After PR #2 merges:
1. Keep state_handle and git_handle span propagation (unchanged)
2. Move client handler span propagation into the new accept_handle's loop
3. Add span propagation to the new accept_handle thread itself

The new accept_handle structure:
```rust
let accept_span = tracing::Span::current();
let accept_handle = std::thread::spawn(move || {
    accept_span.in_scope(|| {
        loop {
            // ... accept logic ...
            let client_span = tracing::Span::current();
            std::thread::spawn(move || {
                client_span.in_scope(|| handle_client(...));
            });
        }
    });
});
```

**Acceptance**
- [ ] state_handle has span propagation
- [ ] git_handle has span propagation  
- [ ] accept_handle has span propagation
- [ ] client handler threads have span propagation
- [ ] cargo test passes
- [ ] Traces show proper parent-child relationships across threads

**Files:** src/daemon/run.rs
**Depends on:** PR #2 merge
